<br>
It's a normal <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>expense</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of that person's class to use them, sure.  But why should clerics have to eat the cost of reagents?  It makes absolutely no sense.  If you wipe deep in a zone like Plane of Hate or Akheva Ruins, would it be expected for the person summoning the corpses to pay for all of the coffins out of their own pocket? Of course not.  They are using their spell (which happens to have a cost associated with it) for the benefit of the group.  Peridot cost is no different, and over time, it costs the cleric a hell of a lot more than coffins will cost a necromancer or shadow knight.<br>
 <br>
Having Virtue/Aego/Temperance/Symbol/whatever on everyone in the group benefits everyone in the group by improving everyone's survivability and improving odds of success on a mission and bettering your chances at more loot.  It benefits the entire group, so the entire group should bear the expense.<br>
<br>
By the way, I agree with the general sentiment of the thread that LDoN is great.  Just the fact that you are relatively assured of a group for 90 minutes, without any real obligation to stay longer than that set period of time, is an excellent thing in and of itself. But the potential loot, the coolness of the zones themselves and most of the rest is absolutely fantastic  Also, it's been a relatively smooth expansion release.  A few peeves and snags here and there, but nothing absolutely horrible like the Luclin release.<br>
<br>
Easily my favorite expansion to date. <p>--Velsor<br>
Shadow Knight of Cazic-Thule<br>
Seeker of the Dark Truth<br>
